Male genitalia (
Fig. 8
): Tegumen subrectangular, truncate on posterior margin. Socius approximately half length of tegumen, with sparse short setae. Valva narrowly elongate, with basal excavation approximately 0.33 length of valva; costa obtusely produced before middle; sacculus uniformly narrow, slightly convex, with sparse setae from base to near apex, followed by several short spines distally; neck approximately half maximum width of cucullus; cucullus elongate, approximately 1.5 times length of sacculus, gradually broadened to obtusely rounded apex, with a cluster of short spines beyond neck, with ventral large spine set at basal 0.25 and before apex respectively. Phallus approximately 0.66 length of valva; cornuti consisting of numerous deciduous seta-like needles and two thick spines.

Female genitalia (
Fig. 12
): Sternite VII divided into two subtriangular lateral sclerites connected below ostium bursae, with spinous hump on anterior margin at each side of ostium bursae. Ostium bursae situated in middle of sternite VII, large and ovate, wider than long, densely spinous along lateral margins, its posterior margin sclerotized and spinulose, forming a narrow band representing lamella postvaginalis. Antrum inverted trapezoidal, very large, approximately 0.33 length of ductus bursae; colliculum running from middle to basal 0.25 of ductus bursae; ductus bursae nearly equal length to corpus bursae. Corpus bursae ovate; two signa spiniform, with rounded basal plate; appendix bursae and corpus bursae nearly equal in size; ductus seminalis originating from base of appendix bursae. Sternite VI with posterior margin concave and sclerotized medially (
Fig. 12a
).
